Rage is defined as an intense

41:42.067 --> 41:43.569
or violent type of anger.

41:43.602 --> 41:45.571
(screams)

41:45.604 --> 41:47.673
SINGER: * Ohh

41:47.706 --> 41:52.043
EDDIE: Road rage, office rage,
even airplane rage.

41:52.077 --> 41:54.379
SINGER:
* This time I won't let go

41:54.412 --> 41:55.647
EDDIE: Seems like
the whole world

41:55.681 --> 41:58.149
is on the edge
of snapping lately.

41:58.183 --> 42:01.219
But it's not the only way
we use that word.

42:01.252 --> 42:03.722
A raging fire.

42:03.755 --> 42:06.491
A raging storm.

42:06.524 --> 42:08.927
A rager of a party.

42:08.960 --> 42:12.430
All things
that are out of control.

42:12.463 --> 42:16.101
And maybe that's where
our rage comes from.

42:16.134 --> 42:19.871
A feeling that our world,
our lives

42:19.905 --> 42:21.372
are out of control.

42:21.406 --> 42:23.174
-REYNOLDS: I said don't move!
-MICHAEL: Okay, okay!

42:23.208 --> 42:27.212
EDDIE:
When we feel helpless...

42:27.245 --> 42:29.581
powerless...

42:29.615 --> 42:31.482
weak...

42:35.420 --> 42:38.523
(panting)
Hey, where's Eddie?

42:38.556 --> 42:39.958
LENA:
He said he had other plans.

42:39.991 --> 42:43.561
(cheering)

42:43.595 --> 42:46.464
(grunting)

42:48.600 --> 42:52.237
-(grunts)
-(cheering)

42:52.270 --> 42:54.873
SINGER: * Ohh

42:54.906 --> 42:57.876
(grunts)

42:57.909 --> 43:02.047
SINGER:
